       Returns  information  about  the specified setEditMode parameter in the
       Innovus log file and the console.  The  following  information  is  re-
       turned:

              * Parameter name

              * Current value

              * Type (Boolean, string, and so on)

              * Whether the current value was set by user

       If you do not specify a parameter, the software returns information for
       all of the setEditMode parameters.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each getEditMode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man getEditMode

       <parameter_name>
              Returns  value for the specified setEditMode parameters. You can
              specify one or more parameters.

              See setEditMode for names and descriptions of the parameters you
              can specify.

       -quiet Returns the current settings for the specified parameters in the
              Tcl list format only. If you specify -quiet without any  parame-
              ters, the software returns the current settings of all  setEdit-
              Mode parameters in the Tcl list format.

Examples
              * The following command returns the current value for the setEd-
                itMode  -shape parameter, which specifies the shape associated
                with the wire you draw:

                getEditMode -shape

                -shape STRIPE                 # enums={RING  STRIPE  FOLLOWPIN
                IOWIRE COREWIRE BLOCKWIRE PADRING BLOCKRING FILLWIRE FILLWIRE-
                OPC DRCFILL None}, default=STRIPE

                STRIPE

              *

                The  following command returns the current value of the setEd-
                itMode -via_cut_layer parameter, which specifies the via layer
                name for the via to be created or modified:

                getEditMode -via_cut_layer

                -via_cut_layer V12            # string, default=V12

                V12

